==International career==
Sielis was the captain of [[Cyprus national under-21 football team|Cyprus national team under 21]],<ref name="captain u21">[http://www.balla.com.cy/3/11_UEFA/7805_Sielis_%C2%ABPame_gia_niki_me_Germania%C2%BB <U+03A3><U+03B9><U+03AD><U+03BB><U+03B7><U+03C2>: "<U+03A0><U+03AC><U+03BC><U+03B5> <U+03B3><U+03B9><U+03B1> <U+03BD><U+03AF><U+03BA><U+03B7> <U+03BC><U+03B5> <U+0393><U+03B5><U+03C1><U+03BC><U+03B1><U+03BD><U+03AF><U+03B1>"], balla.com.cy, Retrieved 14 November 2011</ref> with 8 appearances and 2 goals. On 03 September 2010 Sielis scored his first goal with the [[Cyprus national under-21 football team|national team under 21]] in a away victory 1-3 over [[Norway national under-21 football team|Norway under-21 football team]].<ref>[http://www.transfermarkt.co.uk/en/norway-u21-cyprus-u21/index/spielbericht_970586.html Norway U21 - Cyprus U21: 1-3 match analysis], transfermarkt.co.uk, Retrieved 30 September 2010</ref>

On 26 March 2010, Sielis made his debut with the national team of Cyprus in the home draw 0-0 againsgt [[Iceland Football Association|Iceland]].<ref>[http://www.transfermarkt.co.uk/en/valentinos-sielis/leistungsdaten/spieler_123627_2010.html Cyprus - Iceland: 0-0 match analysis], transfermarkt.com.uk, Retrieved 26 March 2010</ref> in 2012/13, Sielis played in 2 of national tema matches, in a home victory 1-0 against [[Iceland Football Association|Iceland]], and in away defeat 2-1 from [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]].<ref>[http://www.transfermarkt.co.uk/en/valentinos-sielis/leistungsdaten/spieler_123627_2012.html Valentinos Sielis stats 2012/12], transfermarkt.co.uk</ref>

